nd lane 3 is necrotic DNA.  In panel B, a pulsed-field gel, lanes 1 2 and 3 are untreated, apoptotic, and necrotic, respectively.<\/p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/0Dgqg.gif\" alt=\"Here's a nifty image from the paper\"><\/p>\n","answer_id":9585,"question_id":9583,"up_vote_count":5}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/9583/molecular-indicators-of-apoptosis-clarification-needed","last_activity_date":1375377960,"creation_date":1375376277,"answer_count":1,"title":"molecular indicators of apoptosis: clarification needed","body":"<p>I understand that DNA fragmentation is a molecular indicator of apoptosis. What distinguishes this as a hallmark of programmed cell death, versus one of necrosis?<\/p>\n","question_id":9583,"tags":["death","apoptosis"],"score":3,"accepted_answer_id":9585,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":326,"up_vote_count":3,"last_edit_date":1375377204},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/ZsHrH.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4150,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4150/emi-matro","reputation":155,"display_name":"Emi Matro"},"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/KD6Fx.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":3952,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3952/oreotrephes","reputation":4267,"display_name":"Oreotrephes","accept_rate":86},"score":2,"is_accepted":true,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/ZsHrH.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4150,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4150/emi-matro","reputation":155,"display_name":"Emi Matro"},"score":0,"post_id":9581,"edited":false,"creation_date":1375373027,"comment_id":12595,"body":"&quot;insoluble&quot; is a big clue, I&#39;m dense today. Thanks for the input and link."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/KD6Fx.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":3952,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com