 be explained easily by different reasons, for example they are used to human as a source of their food, so they naturally go close to them.)<\/p>\n\n<p>So my question is:<\/p>\n\n<p><strong>Are there some kinds of animals who have primarily movement based vision? If yes, which animals are examples for this?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>The Michael Crichton's novel has been widely discussed online, I found for example <a href=\"http://jurassicpark.wikia.com/wiki/Tyrannosaurus_rex#Eyesight_Debate\">this<\/a> and several answers at <a href=\"http://answers.yahoo.com/question/index?qid=20061217193648AASG0Fp\">Yahoo Answers<\/a>. Frogs and reptiles are mentioned there. <\/p>\n","question_id":9271,"tags":["zoology","vision"],"score":6,"accepted_answer_id":9280,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":2475,"up_vote_count":6,"last_edit_date":1373787529},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/b219b646efa3c74061977c39306c1841?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":810,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/810/shep","reputation":1198,"display_name":"Shep","accept_rate":67},"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/3bb465ba7c2338b41ef15a2a05306a7c?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":444,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/444/gianpaolo-r","reputation":3120,"display_name":"Gianpaolo R","accept_rate":40},"score":6,"is_accepted":false,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/b219b646efa3c74061977c39306c1841?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":810,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/810/shep","reputation":1198,"display_name":"Shep","accept_rate":67},"score":0,"post_id":2083,"edited":false,"creation_date":1336048047,"comment_id":2718,"body":"Very interesting, so a white light may mess up my sleep patterns? So is the answer to the night-vision question &quot;no&quot;, &quot;maybe&quot;, or &quot;inco